title: Lianne La Havas on Shoes PDTV x265-MVGroup
description:
Musician and fashion icon Lianne La Havas takes us on a Private View of the Victoria and Albert Museum exhibition 'Shoes: Pleasure and Pain', where she gets after-hours access to the amazing show.

Lianne reveals the artistic and social history of footwear, with the exhibition displaying 200 shoes ranging from gold leaf Ancient Egyptian flip flops and the platforms that tripped up Naomi Campbell, to the latest extraordinary contemporary designs.
